    "authoring_instructions": "Write scenario-based forced-choice questions for a neurodivergent-friendly audience where ADHD, ASD, or AuDHD may be common. Each question must present a real tradeoff or deficit, avoid yes/no preference prompts, and stay literal, behaviorally concrete, and low-inference. Include sensory load, routines, task initiation, transitions, recovery time, and communication clarity when relevant. Do not assume eye contact, spontaneity, clutter tolerance, multitasking, or indirect hints are universally positive. Assign a 4-number vector in the order [safety, resource, resonance, expansion]. Negative values are allowed when an option actively moves away from a dimension. Keep all options plausible and mutually exclusive."
